article.headline: Pacific 80, UC Davis 65
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Senior guard Chad Troyer came off the bench to score 16 points, including four behind the arc, to lead Pacific over UC Davis 80-65 on Saturday night. Anthony Brown and Michael Kirby had 15 points each for the Pacific Tigers (12-7, 5-3 Big West), who have beaten UC Davis 46 straight times, dating back to the 1940-41 season. Vince Oliver had 20 points for the UC Davis Aggies (9-12, 4-4 Big West), who trails Pacific in the series 74-10. The Tigers led 24-20 with 3:04 left in the second half until Mark Payne made a free throw, an alley-oop dunk and two more shots from the free throw line to give the Aggies a 25-24 margin. Including Payne's five points, the Aggies finished the first half with a 10-4 run to lead 30-26 at halftime. The Aggies led by six points early in the second half, but the Tigers staged a commanding 14-0 run capped off with a basket by Joe Ford to give Pacific a 47-37 lead at the 11:29 mark. The Tigers built their biggest lead at 72-57 with 2:26 left to play. After Oliver made a lay up with 1:17 left in the game, the Aggies had failed to score a basket from the floor since the 10:38 mark, staying alive with 17 free throws within that span. The Tigers held the Aggies to six field goals in the second half.
